-- India's Biocon to Invest $323 Million on Biotechnology Plant in Malaysia
-- B y   B a r r y   P o r t e r
-- 2010-10-25T09:09:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-25/india-s-biocon-to-invest-323-million-on-biotechnology-plant-in-malaysia.html
Biocon Ltd., India’s biggest
biotechnology company, plans to invest 1 billion-ringgit ($323
million) in a manufacturing facility in Malaysia’s southern
Johor state, according to a media invitation sent by the company
today.  This will be Biocon’s first overseas plant, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Barry Porter at 
 bporter10@bloomberg.net  